title: Samsung SSD missing component (resistor?) but still work?
message:
Sometimes we get a used SSD with a missing resistor or two. (Samsung MZ-JPV128S) Its always the same two resistors, one or both missing.
The thing is the SSD seem to work fine without them, passing diagnostics and performing normally.
Can someone shed some light on what's going on here?  Are they unused vestiges of higher density SSD's?  Will it effect reliability or performance in any way?

[ATTACH type="full" width="30%"]31500._xfImport[/ATTACH]

title: Samsung SSD missing component (resistor?) but still work?
message: It's just a decoupling cap, don't worry about it.
